 (4,0,0,'ebulletin','e-Bulletin','&lt;h2 class=&quot;LNE_title&quot;&gt;e-Bulletin&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issue 1:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://4d4life.org/userfiles/4D4Life%20e-bulletin.pdf&quot;&gt;September 2009&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issue 2:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/userfiles/4D4Life e-bulletin Issue 2 April 2010 FV.pdf&quot;&gt;April  2010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Issue 3: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/userfiles/4D4Life e-bulletin Issue 3 September 2010 HIGH RES.pdf&quot;&gt;September 2010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bgci.org/resources/4d4life/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Subscribe to the 4d4life e-Buletin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','',0),
 (7,0,0,'servicesteam','Services team','&lt;h2 class=&quot;LNE_title&quot;&gt;Services team&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Sara Oldfield is the chair of the Services Team that coordinates the selection and delivery of the array of new services - involving WP 2, WP 3, WP 5 and WP 6.&lt;/p&gt;','','',0),
 (8,0,0,'designteam','Design team','&lt;h2&gt;Design team&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Alex Hardisty is the chair of the Systems Design Team that coordinates the design of systems across the project - involving WP 4, WP 5, WP 6, WP 7, as well as work with the Services Team.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;First Design Team meeting was held on 16 June 2009 in the University of Reading.&lt;/p&gt;','','',0),
 (4,0,0,'Projectsummary','Summary','&lt;h2 class=&quot;LNE_title&quot;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;','Details of the 4d4life project','',0),
 (16,0,0,'summary','Summary','&lt;h2 class=&quot;LNE_title&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: large;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;4D4Life Project Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A coherent classification and species checklist of the world&amp;rsquo;s plants, animals, fungi and microbes&lt;/strong&gt; is fundamental for accessing information about biodiversity. The Catalogue of Life provides the world with a unique service: a dynamically updated global index of validated scientific names, synonyms and common names integrated within a single taxonomic hierarchy.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Catalogue of Life was initiated as a European Scientific Infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt; under FP5 and has a distributed knowledge architecture. Its federated e-compendium of the world&amp;rsquo;s organisms grows rapidly (now covering well over one million species), and has established a formidable user base, including major global biodiversity portals as well as national biodiversity resources and individual users worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Joint Research Activities in this 4D4Life Project&lt;/strong&gt; will establish the Catalogue of Life as a state of the art e-science facility based on an enhanced service-based distributed architecture. This will make it available for integration into analytical and synthetic distributed networks such as those developing in conservation, climate change, invasive species, molecular biodiversity and regulatory domains. User-driven enhancements in the presentation of distribution data and bio-data will be made.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;In its &lt;strong&gt;Networking Activities 4D4Life&lt;/strong&gt; will strengthen the development of Global Species Databases that provide the core of the service, and extend the geographical reach of the programme beyond Europe by realizing a Multi-Hub Network integrating data from &lt;st1:country-region w:st=&quot;on&quot;&gt;China&lt;/st1:country-region&gt;, &lt;st1:country-region w:st=&quot;on&quot;&gt;New Zealand&lt;/st1:country-region&gt;, &lt;st1:country-region w:st=&quot;on&quot;&gt;Australia&lt;/st1:country-region&gt;, N. America and &lt;st1:place w:st=&quot;on&quot;&gt;&lt;st1:country-region w:st=&quot;on&quot;&gt;Brazil&lt;/st1:country-region&gt;&lt;/st1:place&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Service Activities, the largest part of 4D4Life&lt;/strong&gt;, will create new electronic taxonomy services, including synonymy server, taxon name-change, and download services, plus new educational and popular services, for instance for hand-held devices.&lt;/p&gt;','Project details','',0),
